{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774460213,"nonce":"BLyHn/M0DG+aLRP1dhgD0BGFsu8=","message":"**Null-space analysis results**\n\nScript: scripts/eval_null_space.py (commit on feature/part2.5-analysis branch)\n\n| Model | potent_frac | null_frac | potent/null ratio |\n|-------|------------|-----------|-------------------|\n| std, pert_std=0, no update | 0.024 | 0.976 | 0.024 |\n| std, pert_std=1, no update | 0.013 | 0.987 | 0.013 |\n| std+update r=0.3, pert_std=1 | 0.008 | 0.992 | 0.008 |\n\nSISU effects are 97-99% in the output-null space. The GRU hidden state changes substantially with SISU, but almost entirely in dimensions that don't project through the readout matrix to motor output. Models with loss_update show even stronger null-space confinement (0.008 vs 0.024).\n\nThis confirms the hypothesis: SISU modulates internal dynamics (explaining the ~11% accuracy improvement via feedback gain changes) without changing the feedforward trajectory (explaining the \u003c1% velocity effect).","files":null}]}